Jeanette Chabalala, News24SA police. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bloemfontein &ndash; A 31-year-old man was allegedly raped by five men in a donga at Lusaka section in Makwane village, Free State police said on Thursday. &nbsp;The incident happened on Monday night when the man was on his way home from work in Phuthaditjhaba in the Free State, said police spokesperson Mmako Mophiring. &nbsp;"The suspects were allegedly looking to rob him and when they [didn't] find anything, they decided to rape him," Mophiring said. &nbsp;The suspects were still at large.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.